# DrawQuantPDF Multi-Agent Sync

- Respect branch model: `main` (stable), `integration` (merge train), `feat/aiX-*` (feature work).
- Active sprint profile may use dedicated branches:
  - `feat/ai1-quickwins-cv`
  - `feat/ai2-medium-classic-ml`
  - `feat/ai3-major-foundation`
  - `feat/ai4-data-annotations`
  - `feat/ai5-metrics-eval`
- Keep edits aligned to your ownership zone unless task explicitly requires cross-zone changes.
- Before coding, sync with `origin/integration` using `scripts/sync-worktrees.ps1` when map exists.
- Prefer small, atomic commits with clear intent and rollback-friendly scope.
- For integration, use `scripts/integration-merge.ps1` to merge feature branches and run quality checks.
- Do not mix refactor + feature + docs in one PR unless unavoidable.
- For photo-detection work, avoid speculative refactors: preserve fallback path and add feature flags for risky logic.
- Never invent pipeline contracts; extend existing dataclasses/functions incrementally and verify with `python test_pipeline.py`.

## Required PR checks

- PR includes risk note, test plan, and impacted component list.
- Branch is rebased on latest `origin/integration`.
- Local verification is documented (`compileall`, tests, manual GUI where needed).
- Export/calc behavior is validated with at least one real sample.
- Ownership gate passes: `scripts/check-ownership.ps1`.
